To call unmanaged C/C++ DLL methods from Java using JNI, you don't need to create a duplicate copy of the C++ class or rename all the methods. Instead, you need to create a "bridge" between Java and your existing unmanaged DLL. Here's a step-by-step guide to achieve this:

