### Summary
The issue likely arises because Aspose does not automatically recognize the header/footer in the MHTML file. By inspecting the `Document` object, manually adding headers/footers if necessary, and using the appropriate save options, you should be able to preserve the header/footer content during the conversion. Additionally, ensure that your Aspose library is up-to-date and that the MHTML file is well-formed.

